<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4029&amp;p=5033#p5033"><![CDATA[
<blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />joedw wrote:<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>With the current spec, would it make long term sense to: <br /><br />1. Obsolete using &lt;embed&gt;, especially as a fallback for &lt;object&gt;.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />zcorpan wrote:<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Why?<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />Sorry slow getting back here, but so many whys ...<br /><br />&lt;embed&gt; should be obsoleted because this step would present an excellent way to discourage its use, especially as a fallback content container in an &lt;object&gt; element. </div></blockquote>It's not clear to me that it would be useful to discourage it's use.<br /><br />When you don't need fallback, &lt;embed&gt; is basically equivalent to &lt;object&gt;, just less markup.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />The only possible case for using &lt;embed&gt; is for old browsers that failed to implement &lt;object&gt; in a reasonable way.<br /></div></blockquote><br />No. Another possible case for using &lt;embed&gt; is for including, say, Flash on a page, for all browsers.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />joedw wrote:<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>and I think embed could be dropped and use object instead for this.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />zcorpan wrote:<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Why?<br /></div></blockquote> <br /><br />Because &lt;embed&gt; is really obsolete.</div></blockquote>It's only obsolete if we say that it is obsolete. Per the current spec, it is not obsolete.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />If an author is told about the actual very limited subset of browsers that are out there that need &lt;embed&gt; then the author would probably not use it.<br /></div></blockquote>Actually, a lone &lt;embed&gt; works better cross-browser than a lone &lt;object&gt;.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />I think another great reason to obsolet &lt;embed&gt; is that it is the last remnant of the long string of pairs that sometimes are involved in &lt;embed&gt;.  The other use was in the feature string of .open and that has now been dropped, and in fact ignored, as I last saw it. While ignoring this string is probably not the best idea for &lt;embed&gt; it is simple to recode using &lt;param&gt;s instead.<br /></div></blockquote>I don't follow.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>joedw wrote:</cite><br />Finally, any use of embed can be handled by a straighforward restyling to &lt;object&gt; syntax with &lt;param&gt;s.<br /></div></blockquote>&lt;img&gt; can also be handled by a straightforward restyling to &lt;object&gt; syntax. It doesn't follow that &lt;img&gt; or &lt;embed&gt; should be obsoleted.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Wed Jun 24, 2009 1:57 pm</p><hr />
